_[CMakeLists.txt, line 42 [r1]](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/toxcore/75#-KQTYHTPmjXTzSIMyWh6:-KQTYHTPmjXTzSIMyWh7:b-p7dtaz) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/toxcore/blob/95eae9e186b83152a6138d0bfc6697be60c4e5a9/CMakeLists.txt#L42)):_

> ``` CMake
> pkg_search_module(OPUS      REQUIRED opus     )
> pkg_search_module(SNDFILE            sndfile  )
> pkg_search_module(VPX       REQUIRED vpx      )
> ```

I wonder if grouping them with comments would make CMakeLists.txt more friendly to whoever tries to look into it and understand why all of this is needed, e.g.

``` cmake
# toxcore
pkg_search_module(LIBSODIUM REQUIRED libsodium)
# toxav
pkg_search_module(OPUS      REQUIRED opus     )
pkg_search_module(VPX       REQUIRED vpx      )
# tox-bootstrapd
pkg_search_module(LIBCONFIG          libconfig)
# tests
pkg_search_module(CHECK              check    )
# toxav tests
pkg_search_module(OPENCV             opencv   )
pkg_search_module(SNDFILE            sndfile  )
```

---
